Guide: How to add Quests

Quests Objectives:
 - Killing mobs (Special Mobs, like Undead Knight, Dragon Rider, Sepulchure, Ravenshire Mage etc)
 - Item delivery (Giving items to NPC)
  - Get item from killing
  - Get item from crafting
  - Get item from exploring (Loot chests)
  - Get item from purchasing
 - Going to location
  - To talk to other NPCs
  - To explore
  - To scout out a location
There are 3 main objectives, with sub- objectives, make sure there are almost equal amount of objectives for each stage, make it balanced, like there would be less location objectives and more killing objectives.
These are only the main goals, there would be obstacles in the way like parkour, dungeon, mobs. Make sure you add that, don't that things too hard.

Every quest need 4 components, a event, location, conversation, and characters. Here is an example:
 - Xephos went to school and met his pet Enderman (Location)
 - Xephos: Hello Enderman, could you teleport me home? (Conversation)
 - Enderman: Of course? Hold my hand. (Conversation)
 - Xephos held the Enderman's hand and teleported home. (Event)
 (Characters and introduced throughout the quest)
So that is an example, now follow this format for every quest.

